parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle. The vehicle may surge forward
or continue to accelerate even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle in reverse gear can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, posing a significant risk to the driver, passengers, and others in the vicinity.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably in reverse gear
and may not respond to braking attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Filler Neck Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty design of the fuel tank filler neck can cause fuel to spill out when filling the tank, leading to a fire hazard, environmental damage, and potential harm to people nearby.
symptoms: Fuel spills out when filling the tank
fuel leaks from the filler neck
fuel odor is present near the filler neck.
